sentences: She began her music career as a member of Iluminada, is the founder of the electronic rock band Zigmat, and collaborated in Pacha Massive before forming her own solo project in 2012.
Their debut self-titled album was released in 2007 and became the first stepping stone for the band in the US.
Zigmat has also performed for the LAMC Festival and was chosen as the best emerging artist of LAMC in 2009, also participating at the CMJ festival and SXSW.
In May 2009, Zigmat released Sounds of Machines, their second full-length album in the US.

In 2009, Zigmat signed with Spanish label Actua Musica and began touring for much of that year, performing at Europe's Sonar Festival held in Barcelona, Spain whose appearances also included Radiohead, Air and Sigur Ros.
In 2010, Lionheart dismantled Zigmat and began working with singer, multi-instrumentalist and producer, Ramon Nova of Pacha Massive.
She spent the summer of 2011 in Santorini, Greece where she completed Indian Summer.
In 2012, she made a return to her former label while signing with Latin Alternative music powerhouse, Nacional Records.

Lionheart's Indian Summer was released on April 14, 2012 by Nacional Records and was well received by critics in the U.S. Produced by Alon Leventon and Lionheart, the songs feature Lionheart's acoustic guitar in straightforward arrangements.
In May 2014, Monica continued her solo career while releasing "The Future", a playful, one-off single produced by Yusuke Yamamoto and herself.
She released a video for the track which was premiered on Concert Blogger on June 10, 2014.
Produced by Steve Wall (Pearl and the Beard) with Dan Molad (of Lucius) and Ryan Alfred (of Calexico), Missed Connections was released January 29, 2016.
Produced by Monica Lionheart, the multi-lingual reggaeton flavored album Bodega Beat was released May 28, 2021.
Bodega Beat layers a maelstrom of different styles and samples to create one of the most immersive records that 2021 has heard so far.
